==Templates==
{{expand}}
Enclose a template in double curly braces to have it transcluded to the page.
<pre>{{templatename|parameter1|parameter2}}</pre>
Inside the template file (e.g. [[Template/en/delete]]), access parameters with triple curly braces.
<pre>{{{1}}} {{{2|default}}}</pre>

*Also see [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Template Template help] on Wikipedia.

==Redirects==
Use redirects to have one article automatically forward the read to another. In this example, [[Main/en/checkpoints]] automatically redirects to [[Main/en/waypoints]]:
<pre>#REDIRECT [[Main/en/waypoints]]</pre>

==Categories==
Add articles to a category by adding a category link at the bottom of the article:
<pre>[[Category:en/Development]]</pre>

Display the category as a normal link by adding a colon:
<pre>[[Category/en/Development]]</pre>
[[Category/en/Development]]

